{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"738eea36-389e-4327-9a7b-75b13e4bae34","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm 11.0.100+\ndotnet build            # ensure it compiles\ndotnet test             # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso check your NuGet packages — any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` packages should be updated to their 11.x versions (e.g., `dotnet outdated` or manually in the `.csproj`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51aa1a00-992a-45e6-91c9-662e9aed5188","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":315,"requestId":"B81B:1E3C:A4DB03B:B335C03:69FD400C"},"id":"37ef9c62-eb57-4b66-8d64-a92cfe453dae","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:44:50.899Z","parentId":"64e08cdf-c3b8-4372-b756-b4b96a284b1f"}
